  <description>
    <p>
        Ergonomic support utility that regularly reminds you to take breaks
        from using your computer, similar to tools like Workrave and Safe Eyes.
    </p>
    <p>With Stretch Break you can:</p>
    <ul>
      <li>Get break reminders every 20 minutes</li>
      <li>Automatically pause the break countdown when you're not using your computer</li>
      <li>Automatically reset your break countdown when you've been away long enough</li>
      <li>Mute break reminders for a period of time</li>
      <li>Enable reading mode, where the break countdown doesn't pause while mouse and keyboard are idle</li>
    </ul>
    <p>
      Stretch Break works best with its accompanying GNOME Shell extension installed, which will
      display remaining time in your system tray.
    </p>
  </description>

  <releases>
